defaultIs cycling safe?
defaultAll the statistics tell me cycling is safe, and that’s what I tell our members. But this reflects only cycling as it is carried out today. In 
defaultevery school in Richmond
default, many more children 
defaultwantdefault to cycle to school than currently do so. What’s holding them bac
defaultk? In general, it’s safety: no parent would allow a primary school child to cycle in a cycle lane on an A-road or A-road equivalent – when asked, parents generally list safety concerns as the reason for them not allowing children to get on a bike to school
default.
defaultMy daughter wants to cycle to school, and is capable of making the journey, but I can’t allow her to ride in the gutter with cars, trucks and vans passing by a foot away at up to 30 mph. The only way to make cycling both *seem* and *be* safe for these ve
defaultry vulnerable transport users is to provide safe places to cycle where they are not required to interact constantly with dangerous vehicles.
