defaultWhat can central / local 
defaultGovt
default do to improve cycling safety …
defaultGovernment across the country needs to provid
defaulte safe, continuous, direct routes which make it possible for people to get on their bikes without the need for expensive lighting or clothing: in countries where lots of people cycle, it happens because they can do it without having to continuously interac
defaultt with motor vehicles.
defaultWe’ve tried, for too long, telling people how useful it is to get training, or legislating for safer HGVs, or making cars nicer for when they inevitably drive into people or things. Now let’s try the thing that we know – from plentif
defaultul evidence in Cambridge, as well as 
defaultAssen
default, from Bristol and from Copenhagen – cycling is something everyone can do, if we give them somewhere nice to do it.
